
// This Hyperlambda code snippet adds HTTP headers to a specific [http.post] request. It uses [add] to append the values retrieved by [get-value] from the [headers] node to the headers of the [http.post] request. The expression [x:./*/http.post/*/headers] targets the headers node within the HTTP POST request, and [get-value:x:@.headers/*] fetches the values of the headers to be added.
add:x:./*/http.post/*/headers
   get-value:x:@.headers/*
